record_data.record_plain_text: PANORAMA WIND, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Panorama Wind, LLC ("Panorama Wind") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Panorama Wind generating facility ("Panorama Wind Facility"). Panorama Wind is a solar generating facility located in Weld County, Colorado. The Panorama Wind Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Tri-State Generation and Transmission Association, Inc. ("Tri-State"). This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Panorama Wind's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Panorama Wind Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Panorama Wind's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Panorama Wind shall be subject to Schedule 2 of Tri-State's Open Access Transmission Tariff. MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $260,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $21,666.67.
